Crypt manager is a encrypted folder management tool.
This the Ubuntu Google Summer of Code project of Kévin Dunglas,
mentored by Jani Monoses.

See http://code.google.com/p/crypt-manager/ for details.
Informations about Ubuntu Linux: http://www.ubuntu.com
Informations about Google Summer of Code: http://code.google.com/soc/


!!! READ THIS BEFORE ANY USE !!!
================================
This is a BETA software pulished ONLY FOR TEST !
It can DESTROY your data.
Test it only on BACKUPED directories.

Please send us report using our issues tracker at code.google.com. Don't forget
to attach the traceback (everything displayed in the terminal window).


INSTALL
=======
Depends of:
- Python 2.5
- cryptsetup with LUKS support (apt-get install cryptsetup)

To use gcrypt-manager you also need gtk and pygtk.glade Python modules
(provided by PyGTK)

Type in a shell:
tar xvjpf crypt-manager-0.1.tar.bz2
cd crypt-manager-0.1


GRYPT-MANAGER
=============
Go into the installation directory (i.e: cd ~/cryptmanager-0.1) and type
in a shell:
gksu ./gcrypt-manager


Options:
--crypt [DIRECTORY] [SIZE]  encrypt directory
--open DIRECTORY            open an encrypted folder
--info                      display this help message
--close DIRECTORY           close an encrypted folder
--decrypt DIRECTORY         decrypt encrypted folder
--version                   display version information


CRYPT-MANAGER
=============
Go into the installation directory (i.e: cd ~/cryptmanager-0.1)
You must use this command as root.

Options:
--crypt DIRECTORY SIZE  encrypt directory
--open DIRECTORY        open an encrypted folder
--help                  display this help message
--close DIRECTORY       close an encrypted folder
--decrypt DIRECTORY     decrypt encrypted folder
--version               display version information


Examples :

# Got root
keyes@kirk:~$ sudo -s
Password:

# Create some samples
root@kirk:~/Projects/crypt-manager# mkdir test
root@kirk:~/Projects/crypt-manager# echo "Bonjour" > test/bonjour
root@kirk:~/Projects/crypt-manager# echo "Aurevoir" > test/aurevoir

# Encrypt a directory
root@kirk:~/Projects/crypt-manager# ./crypt-manager --crypt test 60
Password: azerty

[...]

# List the content of the directory unmounted
root@kirk:~/Projects/crypt-manager# ls test

# Open the encrypted directory
root@kirk:~/Projects/crypt-manager# ./crypt-manager --open test
Password: azerty

# List the content of the mounted encrypted directory
root@kirk:~/Projects/crypt-manager# ls test
aurevoir  bonjour  lost+found

# Close it
root@kirk:~/Projects/crypt-manager# ./crypt-manager --close test
# List if content
root@kirk:~/Projects/crypt-manager# ls test

# Decrypt it
root@kirk:~/Projects/crypt-manager# ./crypt-manager --decrypt test
Password: azerty
aurevoir  bonjour  lost+found


